A: You can use Handler and postDelayed() method to pause your thread.
Here is an example:
new Handler().postDelayed(new Runnable() {
    @Override
    public void run() {
        // This is where you want to pause your thread
        // Change the button background here
    }
}, 1000); // 1000 is the delay time in milliseconds

In your case, you can use it like this:
new Handler().postDelayed(new Runnable() {
    @Override
    public void run() {
        thisbutton.setBackgroundResource(R.drawable.defaultcard);
    }
}, 1000);


A: You can use the postDelayed method of the Handler class.
Here is an example:
new Handler().postDelayed(new Runnable() {
    @Override
    public void run() {
        thisbutton.setBackgroundResource(R.drawable.defaultcard);
    }
}, 1000);

In this example, the Runnable will be executed after a delay of 1000 milliseconds (1 second).

